1 c. A resident who is eligible for a license under this subsection may transfer that
2 eligibility for the license to a spouse or legal dependent residing customarily with
3 the resident, but no more than one license may be issued under this subsection
4 for any qualifying land. A resident transferring eligibility under this subsection may
5 not receive a license under this subsection for the season for which eligibility was
6 transferred. If not otherwise specified in an agricultural lease, the landowner is
7 entitled to receive the license.
8 d. The number of licenses issued without charge under this subsection may not
9 exceed the total numberone-half of buck licenses prescribed for each district or
10 unit in the governor's proclamation. If the number of eligible persons who apply
11 for licenses issued without charge under this subsection exceeds the number of
12 licenses prescribed for the district or unit in the governor's proclamation less any
13 licenses that are otherwise designated to be issued with a charge under this
14 subsection, the licenses to be issued without charge must be issued by lottery as
15 prescribed in the governor's proclamation. If the number of licenses prescribed
16 for the district or unit in the governor's proclamation exceeds fifty and if the
17 number of applications for these licenses exceeds the number of licenses
18 prescribed for the district or unit in the governor's proclamation, then one-half of
19 the licenses exceeding fifty must be issued by lottery as prescribed in the
20 governor's proclamation and may not be issued to landowners without charge.
